QSM_OEF_Aug18_JCBFM

Ahmed Khalil

13 August 2018

Methods
Linear mixed models were used to investigate:

  • the main effects of hemisphere (contralateral / ischemic) and group (no hypoperfusion / match / large mismatch), as well as their interaction, on the OEF values using the R package “lme4” [1]. The model included varying intercepts for each patient and hemisphere.
  • the relationship between OEF and rCBF in the ischemic hemispheres of patients with large mismatch (with varying intercepts for each patient).
  • the relationship between the distance from the DWI lesion and the OEF value. This included the pattern of hypoperfusion (match vs large mismatch) as a fixed effect (with varying intercepts for each patient).

P-values of the mixed models’ coefficients were calculated using Satterthwaite’s method for approximating degrees-of-freedom (R package “lmerTest” [2]). A visualization of the models was created using the R package “effects” [3]. Marginal and conditional R-squared were calculated using the R package “MuMIn” [4].

References:
[1] Douglas Bates, Martin Maechler, Ben Bolker, Steve Walker (2015). Fitting Linear Mixed-Effects Models Using lme4. Journal of Statistical Software, 67(1), 1-48. doi:10.18637/jss.v067.i01.

[2] Kuznetsova A, Brockhoff PB and Christensen RHB (2017). “lmerTest Package: Tests in Linear Mixed Effects Models.” Journal of Statistical Software, 82(13), pp. 1-26. doi: 10.18637/jss.v082.i13 (URL: http://doi.org/10.18637/jss.v082.i13).

[3] John Fox (2003). Effect Displays in R for Generalised Linear Models. Journal of Statistical Software, 8(15), 1-27. URL http://www.jstatsoft.org/v08/i15/.

[4] Kamil Barton (2018). MuMIn: Multi-Model Inference. R package version 1.42.1. https://CRAN.R-project.org/package=MuMIn

Results
There was no statistically significant main effect of either group (F = 3.18, p = 0.07) or hemisphere (F= 3.98, p = 0.05) on OEF values. The marginal R-squared (fixed effects only) was 0.15 and the conditional R-squared (fixed + random effects) was 0.42. There was a statistically significant interaction between group and hemisphere (F = 5.17, p = 0.008), with the difference in OEF between hemispheres being most prominent in patients with large mismatch (b = 0.04, standard error = 0.018, t = 2.2, p = 0.0315).

There was a statistically significant relationship between rCBF and OEF (b = -0.22, standard error = 0.05, t = -4.74, p = 0.00008). The marginal R-squared (fixed effects only) was 0.45 and the conditional R-squared (fixed + random effects) was 0.61.

There was a statistically significant relationship between rCBF and rOEF (b = -0.9, standard error = 0.21, t = -4.34, p = 0.00016). The marginal R-squared (fixed effects only) was 0.37 and the conditional R-squared (fixed + random effects) was 0.68.

There was a statistically significant interaction between the distance from the DWI lesion to the vein and the perfusion pattern (match / large mismatch) on the OEF values (b = -0.0056, standard error = 0.0012, t = -4.54, p < 0.0001). The marginal R-squared (fixed effects only) was 0.13 and the conditional R-squared (fixed + random effects) was 0.59.
